<br>
Next load your best pillar and a draught.  Fire and magic based is the way to go here.  It really helps to have a spell casting distance focus item as well.  Up on top of the cliffs is where to quad.  There is the port in ring at one end and the rock just before the tower at the other end.  You want to drag your wyverns around the rock.  There is only one cobalt drake that pathes up in that area and the area has good pathing.<br>
<br>
Lets talk about the pull.  This will be an issue for you.  You can not get near them when you pull with temporal flux.  They have a decent mellee range.  At your level they can stun you and hurt you.  Keep your distance and be heading away from them as you temp flux them to aggro.  Take your time in the pull.  Better to make some large circles and longer pull time than to get stunned.<br>
<br>
How many to pull?  I would shoot for 8.  If your mana pool sucks keep it to 4.  Been a long time since I was level 51.  Personnally when farming I pull every one of them in the zone.<br>
<br>
Now some tips.  Screw snaring.  Just long kite them.  Its simple.  You make a very long oval around the rock.  Use your temporal flux staff to gage when they are out of casting range.  Just when the temporal flux staff shows you out of casting range.  Run a sec further.  Stop, and pivot slightly.  While pivoting cast your aoe. (cuts down on interupts)  As soon as cast bar dissappears run your butt off on your kite path.  Many hesitate to long to see the damage roll by and get caught by the mobs.  Also after casting make sure you run away before you curve into the oval path.  <br>
<br>
After some time blasting you will have two piles of bodies.  One at either end of the oval path so to speak.  When the first wyvern dies, you have basically 7 minutes to loot.  If you can not kill them in 7 minutes, then you have to loot as you kite.  This is tricky cause you can only loot one at a time per oval circuit between each corpse pile.  <br>
<br>
Two more things.  Avoid cobalt drakes at your level.  They are casters and can hurt you with spells.  They are easy to out run and lose agro though as they stop alot to blast.  Run real far and camp agro is my suggestion to you.  If one is near the rock while you are kiting make a smaller circle away from it until it pathes away.  It will increase your kite time but it is a fair trade off.  The other thing is if you get a named.  They can not be snared.  They can not be rooted.  But guess what.  They run at the same speed as other wyverns.  So do the same as above.  Except, kill the named first with a draught as they have more hp and take longer to kill.  Also use the looting while kiting trick explained above.  Then kill the rest of your kite.<br>
<br>
Why do it this way?  Cause you can kill more wyverns per mana bar as you dont have to snare or root.  Asd you get good you will learn to pull to the limit of your mana bar allowing you the best exp possible solo.  I also make about a k in pp items per hour more or less.  (varies alot based on how camped the zone is and how much mana regen you have going)  It is also more fun to pull many at one time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Gladorr Icestorm</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
